<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-343-414  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 343 414  OV: 07 342 838.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  July 1989 v8 n13 p174(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ProDesigner Plus VGA. (Orchid Technology) (Hardware Review) (oneof 15 high-performance VGA card evaluations in '16-bit VGA cardsstretch the standard') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poor, Alfred.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Orchid Technology's ProDesigner Plus VGA provides high resolutionwith a low profile.andP;  It provides midrange performance with1,024-by-768 resolution.andP;  This board performs well incompatibility tests and has average benchmark test times.andP;  Itincludes utilities, such as a screen font editor, small textfonts, a BIOS relocation program, an ANSI.SYS-type emulator, andthe Hotkey and Hotzoom utility programs that allow zooming andpanning for examining areas in close-up detail.andP;  This is anattractive value, considering its respectable performance and $599price.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Orchid Technologies (products).andO;Product:   Orchid Technology ProDesigner Plus VGA (Circuit board).andO;Topic:     Video BoardsSpecial-Purpose Boards-CardsBoards-CardsEvaluationComparison.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Fact file. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ProDesigner Plus VGAandM;FACT FILE ProDesigner Plus VGA Orchid Technology, 45365 Northport Loop West,Fremont, CA 94538; (415) 683-0300andM;List Price: $599andM;Requires: 286 or 386 AT-compatible computer, VGA monitor (multiscanningmonitor required for 800 by 600 display resolution).andM;In Short: Average in terms of both price and performance, the ProDesignerPlus VGA is able to display 1,024 by 768 resolution and comes with specialgraphics utilities and high-resolution drivers for seven popular packages.andM;Long, low, and lean, Orchid Technology's ProDesigner Plus VGA gives you highresolution with a low profile.andP;  At a list price of $599, this full-lengthboard will give you displays of up to 1,024 by 768 resolution and midrangeperformance.andM;The board is less than 3 inches tall, making it easy to fit into XT andsmall-footprint cases.andP;  The limited amount of board real estate is part ofthe reason that the card offers only a 15-pin analog port.andP;  But theProDesigner Plus is one of the easiest cards to configure and install; it hasonly two jumpers and no switches.andM;The ProDesigner Plus is built around the Tseng Labs VLSI chip.andP;  The card alsosports three separate BIOS ROM chips and five different crystals.andP;  The 512Kof memory comes in the form of 100-nanosecond chips that are soldered inplace.andP;  Overall the board has a fairly clean design, thanks to its extensiveuse of surface-mount chips.andP;  There is only one extra wire on the back of thecard, indicating minimal last-minute design changes.andP;  Orchid also offers twoother VGA cards.andP;  The Designer VGA is an 8-bit card with 256K RAM; theProDesigner VGA is a 16-bit card with 256K.andM;The ProDesigner Plus performed well in the PC Labs compatibility tests,having only a few register-level flaws.andP;  The most significant was a jumpyresponse to the Pan and Scroll test, which is a problem shared by themajority of the cards tested here.andP;  The benchmark test times were uniformlyaverage compared with those of the competition.andM;The ProDesigner Plus comes with 800 by 600 drivers for Microsoft Windows/286,Ventura Publisher, Lotus 1-2-3, AutoCAD, and other popular programs.andP;  It alsoincludes some handy utilities, such as small text fonts and a screen fonteditor, a BIOS relocation program, and an ANSI.SYS-type emualtor.andP;  Inaddition, the card came with Hotkey and Hotzoom, a handy pair of utilityprograms that allow you to zoom in on a graphics display, then pan around toexamine different areas in close-up detail.andM;The ProDesigner Plus is one of the least expensive 512K boards you can buy,and when you factor in its respectable benchmark test performance, it comesout as one of the more attractive values in the field.andO;</TEXT></DOC>